So, these guys don't travel with a doctor?

00:16.787 --> 00:18.687
No, they do... it's just for their horses.

00:18.712 --> 00:20.412
Well, it's a pretty sweet gig.

00:20.437 --> 00:23.137
Yeah, it'd be even sweeter if we
were getting our full of that, right?

00:23.162 --> 00:25.462
That's nice you gave them a break,
I mean they're clearly hurting.

00:25.637 --> 00:28.204
Well, to be totally honest, I, uh...

00:28.206 --> 00:30.173
I cut 'em a deal to make sure
you'd be busy.

00:30.175 --> 00:33.075
You know, keep your mind off,
you know, the breakup.

00:33.077 --> 00:35.278
You mean Christina? That wasn't a breakup.

00:35.280 --> 00:36.612
I know, I know.

00:36.614 --> 00:37.914
I was trying to avoid the word "dumped."

00:37.916 --> 00:39.382
What? I did not get dumped.

00:39.384 --> 00:41.651
We just went our separate ways
after a relationship

00:41.653 --> 00:43.119
that could have been but never really was.

00:43.121 --> 00:44.420
Uh-huh. And the term for that is?

00:44.422 --> 00:46.589
- I... can you just...
- Okay, okay.

00:46.591 --> 00:48.591
I have bigger things
to deal with than your...

00:48.593 --> 00:50.693
whatever it was, anyway.

00:50.695 --> 00:52.328
Guess who's coming to town.

00:52.330 --> 00:54.363
I'd say Santa Claus, but
it's summer and we're jewish.

00:54.365 --> 00:55.498
Yeah, I wish it was Santa Claus.

00:55.500 --> 00:57.066
No, the general. Yeah.

00:57.068 --> 00:58.835
He is detouring off the campaign trail

00:58.837 --> 01:00.369
to get some kind of award,

01:00.371 --> 01:05.007
and Paige thinks it's time
for her parents to meet dad.

01:05.009 --> 01:06.242
Sounds reasonable.

01:06.244 --> 01:07.944
Oh, does it? Reasonable?

01:07.946 --> 01:09.979
Her dad used to be a general.

01:09.981 --> 01:13.382
Our dad used to be in
the general population, Henry.

01:13.384 --> 01:15.017
You're getting married, Evan.

01:15.019 --> 01:17.019
I mean, at some point,
the bride's and groom's

01:17.021 --> 01:19.121
families have to meet.

01:19.123 --> 01:20.990
You're right.

01:20.992 --> 01:22.892
You're absolutely right.

01:22.894 --> 01:24.260
"At some point."

01:24.262 --> 01:25.895
I'll just postpone it. Oh, my God.

01:25.897 --> 01:27.997
Mwah. Henry, you're a genius.

01:27.999 --> 01:29.765
- I wasn't...
- Ha ha!

01:29.767 --> 01:31.334
How does he...

01:31.336 --> 01:32.869
Hah!

01:32.871 --> 01:35.238
That a girl, use your toe, not your heel.

01:35.240 --> 01:36.672
- Hey, guys.
- Hi, Evan.

01:36.674 --> 01:37.773
- Hi.
- Look at us.

01:37.775 --> 01:39.175
We're stomping on divots.

01:39.177 --> 01:40.376
Oh, wow, that's very exciting.

01:40.378 --> 01:41.544
We have to talk.

01:41.546 --> 01:42.912
You know what's exciting?

01:42.914 --> 01:45.514
That I'm going to get to meet
your future in-laws.

01:45.516 --> 01:46.649
We don't need to talk.

01:46.651 --> 01:48.050
That's exciting, dad.

01:48.052 --> 01:49.518
Friday at 6:00. We have reservations.

01:49.520 --> 01:50.720
Ugh, I have them right now.

01:50.722 --> 01:52.588
- Okay, good.
- How about this?

01:52.590 --> 01:56.292
I now have something
in common with Paige's dad.

01:56.294 --> 01:58.261
Yeah, my dad is on his way to Albany

01:58.263 --> 02:00.229
to receive the humanitarian
medal of valor,

02:00.231 --> 02:01.797
and your dad is up for a bloggie.

02:01.799 --> 02:03.332
Oh, a bloggie.

02:03.334 --> 02:05.668
Well, you know, for self-improvement.

02:05.670 --> 02:07.870
Okay, so it's not a humanitarian award.

02:07.872 --> 02:11.374
But I figure since
I have a little prison time,

02:11.376 --> 02:14.010
my chances are pretty good.

02:14.012 --> 02:15.978
- Good luck, pop.
- Thank you.

02:15.980 --> 02:18.180
- Hello, all.
- Hi.

02:18.182 --> 02:19.348
Enjoying the match?

02:19.350 --> 02:20.549
Yeah.

02:20.551 --> 02:22.385
Well, you know, guys ridin' on horses,

02:22.387 --> 02:25.288
swingin' at balls... what?

02:25.290 --> 02:27.189
- That's the game, isn't it?
- Basically.

02:27.191 --> 02:29.091
I've been to the tournament
nine years running.

02:29.093 --> 02:31.560
And I've never been here
because horses terrify me.

02:31.562 --> 02:33.329
But speaking of getting back on the horse,

02:33.331 --> 02:34.730
Divs, how was your date last night?

02:34.732 --> 02:36.032
Evan, that's personal.

02:36.034 --> 02:37.199
No, it's not.

02:37.201 --> 02:38.534
Unless there was some...

02:38.536 --> 02:39.902
You know... what? Then it would be...

02:39.904 --> 02:42.405
was there any...
You know, was there?

02:42.407 --> 02:44.173
- There was not.
- Oh.

02:44.175 --> 02:46.609
There was barely... I know.

02:46.611 --> 02:48.444
Mm, sounds like you didn't like him.

02:48.446 --> 02:49.812
I liked him fine...

02:49.814 --> 02:52.081
just like I have liked the other two guys

02:52.083 --> 02:53.549
that I have been set up with.

02:53.551 --> 02:55.017
Yeah, but who's looking for like?

02:55.019 --> 02:56.485
- Dre... wh...

02:56.487 --> 02:58.087
Okay.

02:58.089 --> 02:59.322
- Ooh, excuse me.
- Excuse me.

02:59.324 --> 03:00.556
Sorry.

03:00.558 --> 03:02.491
- New shoes.
- Wow. Yow.

03:02.493 --> 03:03.826
Those are some tall new shoes.

03:03.828 --> 03:05.728
Are you stomping divots,
or are you making them?

03:05.730 --> 03:07.596
I'm so...

03:07.598 --> 03:09.332
I'm fine. I'm fine. And you know what?

03:09.334 --> 03:12.034
You don't have to rush,
'cause I'm pretty sure

03:12.036 --> 03:14.570
they're not gonna start
till we leave the field.

03:14.572 --> 03:16.672
Oh, I'm not trying to leave the field.

03:16.674 --> 03:18.975
I'm trying to get to Rafa.

03:18.977 --> 03:21.877
Is he the one who's riding

03:21.879 --> 03:25.614
the beautiful chestnut quarter-horse?

03:25.616 --> 03:27.717
You're looking at his horse? Wow.

03:27.719 --> 03:29.251
I like horses.

03:29.253 --> 03:31.220
Certainly draws a crowd, doesn't he?

03:31.222 --> 03:32.588
Well, have you seen him?

03:32.590 --> 03:34.323
He's 50 shades of, "oh, my God."

03:34.325 --> 03:35.791
"Take me. Take me now."

03:35.793 --> 03:37.827
Oh, I'm guessing
you're not here for the polo.

03:37.829 --> 03:39.228
Polo, shmolo.

03:39.230 --> 03:40.329
Oh, I see an opening.

03:40.331 --> 03:42.498
Nice to meet you all.

03:42.500 --> 03:45.501
Who knew polo players had groupies?

03:46.937 --> 03:49.238
Rafa! Hello, Raf... no!

03:49.240 --> 03:53.242
You... you're playing very well, Rafa.

04:00.618 --> 04:02.485
- Hey, guys.
- Hey.

04:02.487 --> 04:04.053
So, uh, who's winning?

04:04.055 --> 04:06.856
Oh, the, uh... the guys on the, uh, hor...

04:06.858 --> 04:08.090
the, uh... with the m...

04:08.092 --> 04:10.059
I have no idea who's winning.

04:10.061 --> 04:11.460
Okay, thank you.

04:11.462 --> 04:12.928
So are you going to the dinner?

04:12.930 --> 04:15.164
- The dinner?
- Mm-Hmm, Paige's family.

04:15.166 --> 04:16.531
Oh, that.

04:16.534 --> 04:17.933
Uh, no.

04:17.935 --> 04:19.334
I mean, we've met.

04:19.337 --> 04:21.103
You know, I think that
should just be you guys.

04:21.105 --> 04:23.572
If you change your mind,
or if you get lonely,

04:23.574 --> 04:25.274
you call me immediately.

04:25.276 --> 04:27.576
Uh, why would I feel lonely?

04:27.578 --> 04:29.178
Because your brother
just told me you were dumped.

04:29.180 --> 04:30.679
I did not get dumped.

04:30.681 --> 04:32.381
- He did not get dumped.
- You did get dumped.

04:32.383 --> 04:35.084
- You did get dumped?
- I didn't get dumped!

04:41.659 --> 04:42.792
- Ooh.
- Oh!

04:42.794 --> 04:44.193
Simon! Wait, wait.

04:44.195 --> 04:45.995
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Time-out.

04:45.997 --> 04:47.463
- Come on, get up.
- I can't.

04:47.465 --> 04:49.665
- Come on, Simon, get up.
- It hurts too much.

05:13.549 --> 05:18.549
Royal Pains 4x10 - Who's Your Daddy
Original air date August 22, 2012

05:18.574 --> 05:23.574
Sync and corrections by atrn97g
